 Heisenberg Uncertainty Principle
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\Delta E\Delta t\gtrsim\hbar\label{eq:heisenberguncertainty}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta E$
\end_inset

 is the energy of the particle and 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta t$
\end_inset

 is the time which the particle exists.
 As an example, consider a neutrino of energy of 1 GeV emitting a Z-boson
 of off-shell energy, 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta E=1$
