\begin_layout Standard
Traveling through matter has the potential to increase the sensitivity of
 oscillation measurements if the baseline is long enough.
 Known as the Mikheyev-Smirnov-Wolfenstein (MSW) effect, all oscillations
 are affected by coherent forward scattering of neutrinos with electrons
 in the media.
 Taking the example of 
\begin_inset Formula $\nuantinuparticle{\mu}\rightarrow\nuantinuparticle e$
\end_inset

 from 
